== Tomato Salsa ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @Red Onion{1%unit}. Thinly slice one half. Finely dice other half until you have 2 TBSP diced onion. Quarter @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Zest @Lime{1%unit} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into halves. Core, seed, and remove white ribs from @Red Bell Pepper{1%unit}, then thinly slice. Chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, toss together diced onion, tomatoes, lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and half the cilantro. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Set aside until meal is ready.

> If you'll be warming your tortillas in the #oven{} and not the #microwave{}, now is a good time to preheat it to 400 degrees.

== Fajita Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and bell pepper. Cook until softened and slightly blistered, ~{4-5%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Thinly slice @Pork Chops{12%ounce} against the grain into strips. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. When veggies are done, remove from pan and set aside. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add as much pork as will fit without overcrowding (you may need to work in batches). Cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and nearly cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Return veggies and all pork to pan along with @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lime juice. Cook, tossing, until pork is no longer pink in center, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Tortillas ==

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6%unit} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

== Fajita Bar ==

When everything is ready, set up a station for the fajitas. Place salsa, filling, tortillas, @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}, and remaining cilantro in individual plates or bowls and invite everyone to assemble their own fajitas.